member.remarks:
            Endpoints used:


GET /v2/corporate-actions/announcements?ca_types=dividend&symbol={ticker}

GET /v2/corporate-actions/announcements?ca_types=split&symbol={ticker}

            The Alpaca announcements endpoint requires a Broker API key pair or a standard
            Alpaca data subscription.  Requests are authenticated via the APCA-API-KEY-ID
            and APCA-API-SECRET-KEY headers read from the environment / configuration.

API Documentation:
  Chain snapshot:    GET /v1beta1/options/snapshots/{underlying_symbol}
  Contract details:  GET /v1beta1/options/contracts/{symbol}
  Available tickers: GET /v1beta1/options/contracts?underlying_symbols={symbol}
Reference: https://docs.alpaca.markets/reference/optionsnapshots

API Documentation:
  Chain snapshots:   GET /v3/snapshot/options/{underlyingAsset}
  Single contract:   GET /v3/snapshot/options/{underlyingAsset}/{optionsTicker}
  Expirations:       GET /v3/reference/options/contracts?underlying_ticker={symbol}

member.summary:
Extension methods for  to simplify property extraction.
Reduces boilerplate TryGetProperty patterns across provider implementations.

Example usage:

// Before
var sym = elem.TryGetProperty("S", out var sProp) ? sProp.GetString() : null;
var price = elem.TryGetProperty("p", out var pProp) ? pProp.GetDecimal() : 0m;

// After
var sym = elem.GetStringOrNull("S");
var price = elem.GetDecimalOrDefault("p");
